<chapter xml:id="getting-started" xreflabel="Getting Started" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"
    xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="5.1">
    <title>Getting Started</title>
    <para>The best way to get started using &productshort; is to make yourself familiar with the
        menus and interface. This will give you an understanding of what features and functions are
        available and how to find them when using the program. Once familiar, it is recomended that
        you adjust the basic settings available in the <guilabel>Preferences</guilabel>.</para>
    <para condition="desktop">This chapter is about getting you aquainted with &productdesktop;
        edition. It gives you a quick tour of the Main Workspace of &productshort; including the
        Main Menu and View Panels. It also covers setting of the preferences so that you may
        configure &productshort; to work with the setting options of your choice.</para>
    <sect1 condition="desktop" xml:id="desktop-main-workspace" xreflabel="Main Workspace">
        <title>Main Workspace</title>
        <para>The &productshort; workspace is comprised of a <xref xlink:href="#main-menu"/> and
                <xref xlink:href="#view-panels"/>.</para>
        <sect2 xml:id="main-menu" xreflabel="Main Menu">
            <title>Main Menu</title>
            <para>Each menu on the Main Menu displays a list of menu items. Menus may be accessed
                using a mouse pointer or accelerator keys.</para>
            <variablelist>
                <varlistentry>
                    <term><guimenu>File</guimenu> (<keycombo>
                            <keycap>Alt</keycap>
                            <keycap>F</keycap>
                        </keycombo>)</term>
                    <listitem>
                        <variablelist>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guimenuitem>New logbook</guimenuitem> (<keycombo>
                                        <keycap>Ctrl</keycap>
                                        <keycap>N</keycap>
                                    </keycombo>)</term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Starts a new empty logbook. </para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                        </variablelist>
                        <variablelist>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guimenuitem>Open Logbook</guimenuitem> (<keycombo>
                                        <keycap>Ctrl</keycap>
                                        <keycap>O</keycap>
                                    </keycombo>)</term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Displays the <guilabel>Open file</guilabel> dialog that
                                        lists previously saved logbook files and enables opening of
                                        a selected logbook file.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                        </variablelist>
                        <variablelist>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guimenuitem>Save</guimenuitem> (<keycombo>
                                        <keycap>Ctrl</keycap>
                                        <keycap>S</keycap>
                                    </keycombo>)</term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Saves the current open logbook.</para>
                                    <para>When a logbook has never been saved, this behaves like a
                                            <guimenuitem>Save as</guimenuitem> operation.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                        </variablelist>
                        <variablelist>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guimenuitem>Save as</guimenuitem> (<keycombo>
                                        <keycap>Ctrl</keycap>
                                        <keycap>V</keycap>
                                    </keycombo>)</term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Displays the Save as dialog that enables saving of the
                                        current open logbook to a new logbook file.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                        </variablelist>
                        <variablelist>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guimenuitem>Open cloud storage</guimenuitem></term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Connects to the &productcloud;, fetches data and displays
                                        divelogs.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                        </variablelist>
                        <variablelist>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guimenuitem>Save to cloud storage</guimenuitem></term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Connects to the &productcloud;, sends data changes to the
                                        cloud storage.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                        </variablelist>
                        <variablelist>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guimenuitem>Cloud storage online</guimenuitem></term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Toggles saving of the current logbook between local cache
                                        and cloud storage.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                        </variablelist>
                        <variablelist>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guimenuitem>Close</guimenuitem> (<keycombo>
                                        <keycap>Ctrl</keycap>
                                        <keycap>W</keycap>
                                    </keycombo>)</term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Closes the current open logbook without exiting
                                        &productshort;</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                        </variablelist>
                        <variablelist>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guimenuitem>Export</guimenuitem> (<keycombo>
                                        <keycap>Ctrl</keycap>
                                        <keycap>E</keycap>
                                    </keycombo>)</term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Displays the <guilabel>Export dive log files</guilabel>
                                        dialog that can be used to export &productshort; logfile
                                        format to file formats used by other divelog programs,
                                        exchange formats and presentation formats.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                        </variablelist>
                        <variablelist>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guimenuitem>Print</guimenuitem> (<keycombo>
                                        <keycap>Ctrl</keycap>
                                        <keycap>P</keycap>
                                    </keycombo>)</term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Displays the <guilabel>Print</guilabel> dialog that can be
                                        used to define print layout options, preview results and
                                        send data to a printer.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                        </variablelist>
                        <variablelist>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guimenuitem>Preferences</guimenuitem> (<keycombo>
                                        <keycap>Ctrl</keycap>
                                        <keycap>,</keycap>
                                    </keycombo>)</term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Displays the <guilabel>Preferences</guilabel> dialog that
                                        can be used to set user preferences related to various
                                        functional areas of the software.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                        </variablelist>
                        <variablelist>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guimenuitem>Find moved media files</guimenuitem></term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para/>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                        </variablelist>
                        <variablelist>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guimenuitem>Configure dive computer</guimenuitem> (<keycombo>
                                        <keycap/>
                                        <keycap>Shift</keycap>
                                        <keycap>C</keycap>
                                    </keycombo>)</term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Displays the <guilabel>Configure dive computer</guilabel>
                                        dialog that can be used to define communication and settings
                                        properties for various dive computer types.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                        </variablelist>
                        <variablelist>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guimenuitem>Recent Logbooks</guimenuitem></term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Lists four of the most recent logbooks to be opened in
                                        order most to least recent.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                        </variablelist>
                        <variablelist>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guimenuitem>Quit</guimenuitem> (<keycombo>
                                        <keycap>Ctrl</keycap>
                                        <keycap>Q</keycap>
                                    </keycombo>)</term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Terminates &productshort;.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                        </variablelist>
                    </listitem>
                </varlistentry>
                <varlistentry>
                    <term><guimenu>Edit</guimenu> (<keycombo>
                            <keycap>Alt</keycap>
                            <keycap>E</keycap>
                        </keycombo>)</term>
                    <listitem>
                        <variablelist>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guimenuitem>Undo</guimenuitem> (<keycombo>
                                        <keycap>Ctrl</keycap>
                                        <keycap>Z</keycap>
                                    </keycombo>)</term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Reverts the most recent changes made to an unsaved logbook
                                        from most to least recent.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guimenuitem>Redo</guimenuitem> (<keycombo>
                                        <keycap>Ctrl</keycap>
                                        <keycap>Shift</keycap>
                                        <keycap>Z</keycap>
                                    </keycombo>)</term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Roles back most recent changes undone by an
                                            <guimenuitem>Undo</guimenuitem> operation to an unsaved
                                        logbook from most to least recent.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                        </variablelist>
                    </listitem>
                </varlistentry>
                <varlistentry>
                    <term><guimenu>Import</guimenu> (<keycombo>
                            <keycap>Alt</keycap>
                            <keycap>I</keycap>
                        </keycombo>)</term>
                    <listitem>
                        <variablelist>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guimenuitem>Import from dive computer</guimenuitem> (<keycombo>
                                        <keycap>Ctrl</keycap>
                                        <keycap>D</keycap>
                                    </keycombo>)</term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Displays the <guilabel>Download from dive
                                            computer</guilabel> dialog that enables selection of
                                        specific dive computer to download from and setting of
                                        download options.</para>
                                </listitem>
                            </varlistentry>
                            <varlistentry>
                                <term><guimenuitem>Import from log files</guimenuitem> (<keycombo>
                                        <keycap>Ctrl</keycap>
                                        <keycap>I</keycap>
                                    </keycombo>)</term>
                                <listitem>
                                    <para>Displays the <guilabel>Open dive log file</guilabel>
                                        dialog that enables listing and selection of log files
