    <sect1 xml:id="setting-preferences" xreflabel="Setting Preferences">
        <title>Setting Preferences</title>
        <para condition="desktop">The <guilabel>Preferences</guilabel> dialog enables setting of
            your personal preferences and requirements when working with &productdesktop;. Settings
            saved in the <guilabel>Preferences</guilabel> will remain persistant for all future
            sessions of the program. Settings within the <guilabel>Preferences</guilabel> dialog are
            grouped as follows:</para>
        <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para><xref xlink:href="#general-settings"/></para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para><xref xlink:href="#unit-settings"/></para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para><xref xlink:href="#language-settings"/></para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para><xref xlink:href="#profile-settings"/></para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para><xref xlink:href="#georeference-settings"/></para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para><xref xlink:href="#network-settings"/></para>
            </listitem>
        </itemizedlist>
        <para>Select <menuchoice>
                <guimenu>File</guimenu>
                <guimenuitem>Preferences</guimenuitem>
            </menuchoice> to display the <guilabel>Preferences</guilabel> dialog.</para>
        <sect2 xml:id="general-settings" xreflabel="General Settings">
            <title>General Settings</title>
            <para>The <guilabel>General</guilabel> settings group </para>
            <sect3>
                <title>Lists and tables</title>
                <para>The <guilabel>Lists and tables</guilabel> group enables you to select the type
                    and size of font used throughout the user interface. The default font and size
                    is dependant on your operating system defaults.</para>
            </sect3>
            <sect3>
                <title>Dives</title>
                <para>The <guilabel>Dives</guilabel> group enables you to define whether or not you
                    want to use a default file for storing dive logs, options include:</para>
                <variablelist>
                    <varlistentry>
                        <term><guilabel>No default file</guilabel></term>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>Select the <guibutton>No default</guibutton> radio button to disable use of a default log file.</para>
                        </listitem>
                    </varlistentry>
                    <varlistentry>
                        <term><guilabel>Local default file</guilabel></term>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>Select the <guibutton>Local default file</guibutton> radio button to enable use of a default log file. By default &productshort; will define a default path and file name for the default. You may choose to remain with the default suggestion or select a different path and file name.</para>
                        </listitem>
                    </varlistentry>
                    <varlistentry>
                        <term><guilabel>Cloud storage default file</guilabel></term>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>Select the <guibutton>Cloud storage default file</guibutton> radio button to use &productcloud; as the default location for storage.</para>
                        </listitem>
                    </varlistentry>
                </variablelist>
                <para>If you choose to use a default file, then you may choose whether the default
                    storage location is on the local disk or on the &productcloud; storage.</para>
            </sect3>
